Q1 Import Prices and Calculate Log Returns¶

In [30]:
def loadPriceRet(path, columns, period=("04-2020", "12-2020")):
    """Function to load price and calculate log returns"""
    
    df = pd.read_csv(path)
    
    df.index = df['Date'].apply(lambda x: datetime(int(x[:4]), int(x[5:7]), int(x[-2:])))
    
    colToDrop = [col for col in df.columns if col not in columns]
    df.drop(columns=colToDrop, inplace=True)
    
    retSeries = (np.log(df['Adj Close'] / df['Adj Close'].shift(1))) * 100
    df['Log Returns'] = retSeries
    
    df.dropna(inplace=True)
    
    df = df[period[0]:period[1]]
    
    return df

In [45]:
def stationarityTest(data):
    
    _, adfP, _, _, _,_ = sm.tsa.adfuller(data, maxlag=0)
    _, kpssP, _, _    = sm.tsa.kpss(data, nlags=0)

    if (adfP <= 0.05) & (kpssP > 0.05):
        print("Process is stationary!")
    elif ((adfP <= 0.05) & (kpssP <= 0.05)) | ((adfP > 0.05) & (kpssP > 0.05)):
        print("Process may or may not be stationary")
    else:
        print("Process is NOT stationary!")
        
def inverse_difference(history, yhat, interval=1):
    return yhat + history[-interval]

ARMA¶

Q2-Q3¶

Rule: Purchase when returns forecasted to be positive and sell when returns forecasted to be negative

In [49]:
armaMdl = ARIMA(btcQ2['Log Returns'])
armaMdl = armaMdl.fit()

forecast = armaMdl.forecast(steps=btcQ3.shape[0])
# invert the differenced forecast to something usable
history = list(btcQ2['Log Returns'])

btcQ3['ARMA Forecast'] = np.nan

for i, yhat in enumerate(forecast):
    inverted = inverse_difference(history, yhat, btcQ2.shape[0])
    history.append(inverted)
    btcQ3.iloc[i, 2] = inverted
    
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))
btcQ3['Log Returns'].plot(label='Actual')
btcQ3['ARMA Forecast'].plot(label='Forecast')
plt.axhline(y=0, c='r', ls='--', lw=1, label='Forecasted Mean')
plt.title('Q2 ARMA Forecasts on Q3 Actual Data')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

btcQ3['ARMA Strategy Returns'] = ((btcQ3['ARMA Forecast'] > 0) * btcQ3['Log Returns'] - (btcQ3['ARMA Forecast'] < 0) * btcQ3['Log Returns'])
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))
btcQ3['ARMA Strategy Returns'].cumsum().plot(label='Strategy Cumulative Returns')
btcQ3['Log Returns'].cumsum().plot(label='Long Portfolio Cumulative Returns')
plt.legend()
plt.title('Cumulative Returns')
plt.show()

GARCH(1, 1) Model¶

Rule: Purchase when variance forecasted to be higher than Q2 mean variance and short it when variance forecasted to be lower than Q2 mean variance

Q2-Q3¶

In [51]:
garchMDL = arch_model(y=btcQ2['Log Returns'], vol='GARCH', p=1, q=1)
garchMDL = garchMDL.fit()

btcQ2['GARCH Var'] = np.power(garchMDL.resid, 2)
Q2meanVar = np.mean(btcQ2['GARCH Var'])

forecasts = garchMDL.forecast(horizon=btcQ3.shape[0])
btcQ3['GARCH Forecasted Variance'] = forecasts.variance.values[-1, :]

btcQ3['GARCH Strategy Returns'] = ((btcQ3['GARCH Forecasted Variance'] > Q2meanVar) * btcQ3['Log Returns'] - (btcQ3['GARCH Forecasted Variance'] < Q2meanVar) * btcQ3['Log Returns'])
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))
btcQ3['GARCH Strategy Returns'].cumsum().plot(label='Strategy Cumulative Returns')
btcQ3['Log Returns'].cumsum().plot(label='Long Portfolio Cumulative Returns')
plt.legend()
plt.title('Q3 Cumulative Returns')
plt.show()

forecasts = garchMDL.forecast(horizon=btcQ3.shape[0])
btcQ3['GARCH Forecasted Variance'] = forecasts.variance.values[-1, :]

btcQ3['GARCH Strategy Returns'] = ((btcQ3['GARCH Forecasted Variance'] > Q2meanVar) * btcQ3['Log Returns'] - (btcQ3['GARCH Forecasted Variance'] < Q2meanVar) * btcQ3['Log Returns'])
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))
btcQ3['GARCH Strategy Returns'].cumsum().plot(label='Strategy Cumulative Returns')
btcQ3['Log Returns'].cumsum().plot(label='Long Portfolio Cumulative Returns')
plt.legend()
plt.title('Cumulative Returns')
plt.show()

Cointegration¶

In [150]:
def egciCointTest(x, y):
    
    _, egts, _ = coint(x, y, maxlag=0)
    
    if egts <= 0.05:
        
        print("Prices pair are cointegrated")
    
    else:
        
        print("Prices pair are NOT cointegrated")
        
def johansenTest(data):
    johansen = coint_johansen(data, 1, 0)
    res = (johansen.trace_stat > johansen.trace_stat_crit_vals)[:-1, :].any(axis=0)
    
    if res.any():
        print("Prices may be cointegrated.")
        print(johansen.trace_stat)
        print('='*20)
        print(johansen.trace_stat_crit_vals)
    else:
        print("Prices are NOT cointegrated")
    
    return johansen.eig, johansen.evec
